Angular artery","Deep temporal artery","Superficial temporal artery"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperficial temporal artery\u003C/strong\u003E (image) is a terminal branch of the external carotid artery that supplies the temporal and frontal regions of the scalp.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emiddle meningeal artery\u003C/strong\u003E is a branch of the maxillary artery that supplies the dura mater and skull, not the scalp\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esupraorbital artery\u003C/strong\u003E is a branch of the ophthalmic artery (from the internal carotid artery) that supplies the forehead\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eangular artery\u003C/strong\u003E is the terminal branch of the facial artery that supplies the medial canthal region\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edeep temporal artery\u003C/strong\u003E is a branch of the maxillary artery that supplies the temporalis muscle\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The superficial temporal artery is a terminal branch of the external carotid artery that supplies the temporal and frontal scalp regions.","The scalp has a rich arterial supply with multiple anastomoses, one of the reasons why scalp wounds bleed profusely."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u201cExternal carotid artery\u201d by Mikael H\u00e4ggstr\u00f6m is under\u00a0Public Domain. \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:External_carotid_artery.png\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63287"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18652"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[